         <listPerson>
            <person xml:id="pers1289">
               <p>A graduate of St. Edmund Hall, <placeName>Oxford</placeName>, Lewis was master of
                  the school at <placeName>Tetbury</placeName> (<date from="1705" to="1712"
                     >1705–12</date>); then rector of <placeName>Great Chalfield</placeName> and
                  curate of <placeName>Holt</placeName> and <placeName>Atford</placeName> (or
                     <placeName>Atworth</placeName>) in <placeName>Wiltshire</placeName> (<date
                     from="1712" to="1761">1712–61</date>). Lewis wrote <persName><ref
                        target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName> in <date when="1746-02-04"
                     >Feb. 4. 1746</date>, attacking his recently-published Parts II-III of the <hi
                     rend="italic">Farther Appeal to the Men of Reason and Religion</hi>, sparking
                  an interchange of several letters between the two men. See <hi rend="italic"
                     >Alumni Oxonienses</hi>; CCEd; and <hi rend="italic">Wesley and Methodist
                     Studies</hi> 7 (<date when="2015">2015</date>): 121–48.</p>
            </person>
         </listPerson>
      </body>
